      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LET'S GO PIES (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Finished second (20.12) at this track last time making it two minors on end. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Deserves a win and gets his chance. ROAD LESS TRAVEL (7) turned in a moderate run last time when fifth at Gawler over 400m behind Hasty Holly (23.52) in a TG1-4W. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Better than last start and can bounce back. ASTON VERONA (2) finds it hard to break through. Finished in the money last time though when second (19.85) at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Can feature again. GOLDEN GANGSTER (8) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
